                    <h2>Meaning and Interpretation</h2>
                    <p>
                        <strong>The Name KARUNA SHANTI (KASH)</strong> – “Karuna Shanti” is a phrase that combines two foundational Sanskrit words: "Karuna" (करुणा), which means compassion, mercy, and kindness, and "Shanti" (शान्ति), which translates to peace, rest, and tranquility.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Therefore, the phrase “Karuna Shanti” is best interpreted as “compassionate peace” or “peaceful compassion.” It signifies a state of inner and outer peace that is achieved through the practice of active kindness and empathy towards all beings.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The abbreviation **“KASH”** serves as a modern and memorable acronym for our organization, embodying these core principles in a single, impactful word that guides all our endeavors.
                    </p>
